==Latin== {{cardinalbox|la| |I|II| |duo|alt=ūnus|ord=prīmus|adv=semel|mult=simplex|dis=singulī|headlink=Appendix:Latin cardinal numbers|wplink=Unus}}
===Alternative forms=== * Symbol: '''I'''
===Etymology=== From {{etyl|OL.|la}} {{term|oinos|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|itc-pro|la}} {{term/t|itc-pro|*oinos}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|la}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*óynos||one, single}}. Cognates include Ancient Greek {{term|sc=polytonic|οἶος|tr=oios|lang=grc}}, Sanskrit {{term|sc=Deva|एक|tr=éka|lang=sa}}, Old Church Slavonic {{term|ѥдинъ|tr=jedinŭ|lang=cu}}, and Old English {{term/t|ang|ān}} (English {{term|one|lang=en}} and {{term|an|lang=en}}).
===Pronunciation=== * {{a|Classical}} {{IPA|/ˈuː.nus/|lang=la}} * {{audio|la-cls-unus.ogg|Audio (Classical)}}
===Numeral=== {{la-num-card|num=1}}
# {{context|cardinal|lang=la}} [[one]]; 1 #* {{RQ:Ovid Metamorphoses|VI|644-645}} #*: satis illi ad fata vel '''unum''' vulnus erat: iugulum ferro Philomela resolvit #*:: "Sufficient was this '''one''' wound to kill; but Philomela also cut open the throat" #* {{RQ:Vulgate|Nehemiae|1|2}} (II Esdrae 1:2) #*: et venit Anani '''unus''' de fratribus meis ipse et viri ex Iuda et interrogavi eos de Iudaeis qui remanserant et supererant de captivitate et de Hierusalem #*:: "and Hanani came, '''one''' of my brethren, he and certain men of Judah; and I asked them concerning the Jews that had escaped, which were left of the captivity, and concerning Jerusalem" #* '''6th c.''' — [[w:Boethius|Boethius]], ''[[s:la:Commentarium in librum Aristotelis Peri hermeneias primae editionis|Commentarium in librum Aristotelis Peri hermeneias primae editionis]]'', Book I, section 5 #*: In summam igitur '''ūnārum''' ōrātiōnum aliae sunt significātiōne '''ūnae''', aliae coniūnctiōne. #*:: "In summary therefore, '''of one''' theme others are (by signification) '''one''', some with connections."
====Usage notes==== See [[Appendix:Latin cardinal numbers#ūnus|Appendix:Latin cardinal numbers]]
====Inflection==== Irregular: similar to first and second declensions but with singular genitives ending in '''-īus''' and singular datives ending in '''-ī'''.
